\label{lem.Popa-intertwining-for-bimodules}
Let $(A,\tau)$ and $(B,\tau)$ be tracial von Neumann algebras and $\bim{A}{H}{B}$ a Hilbert $A$-$B$-bimodule. Then the following are equivalent.
\begin{enumlist}
\item $\{0\}$ is the only closed $A$-$B$-subbimodule of $H$ that is finitely generated as a right Hilbert $B$-module.
\item There exists a net of unitaries $(u_i)_{i \in I}$ in $A$ such that $\lim_{i \in I} \|P_K(u_i \xi)\| = 0$ for every $\xi \in H$ and every finitely generated right Hilbert $B$-submodule $K \subset H$.
\end{enumlist}

